message.content:
**Analysis of the Main Target Image**

1. **Block Count and Layers**  
   - **Total Blocks:** 5  
     • 3 × Orange vertical cylinders (two “legs” plus one “neck”)  
     • 1 × Yellow rectangular prism (“body”)  
     • 1 × Yellow half‐cylinder (“head”)  
   - **Layering (bottom to top):**  
     1) Two vertical orange cylinders on the ground (the “legs”).  
     2) One horizontal yellow rectangular prism bridging across the two legs.  
     3) One vertical orange cylinder set on top of the rectangular prism (the “neck”).  
     4) A yellow half‐cylinder placed atop that neck cylinder (the “head”).  

2. **Spatial Relationships**  
   - The two orange cylinders on the bottom stand parallel and a short distance apart.  
   - The yellow rectangular block rests horizontally across the tops of these two cylinders.  
   - A third orange cylinder sits vertically on the left side of the rectangular block (aligned over one of the legs).  
   - Finally, a yellow half‐cylinder (“head”) is centered on top of that vertical cylinder.  

---

**Selecting the Required Blocks from the Dictionary**

- **Orange Vertical Cylinders:** Index #7 (used three times)  
  (Block #7 is the orange/red cylinder shown standing upright.)  
- **Yellow Horizontal Rectangular Prism:** Index #2 (used once)  
  (Block #2 is the short yellow rectangular block oriented left‐to‐right.)  
- **Yellow Half‐Cylinder (Horizontal Orientation):** Index #10 (used once)  
  (Block #10 is the yellow half‐cylinder with flat side down, curved side up, oriented horizontally.)

Thus, the exact dictionary blocks (with no further rotation) are:  
• Index #7 × 3  
• Index #2 × 1  
• Index #10 × 1  

---

**Assembly Order**

{  
  Step1: Move block with index 7, place it vertically as the first leg.  
  Step2: Move block with index 7, place it vertically as the second leg.  
  Step3: Move block with index 2, place it horizontally across the two leg cylinders.  
  Step4: Move block with index 7, place it vertically on top of the rectangular block (the neck).  
  Step5: Move block with index 10, place it atop the neck cylinder as the head.  
}
